.TH "cnstr_shdsc_ahash" 9 "cnstr_shdsc_ahash" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cnstr_shdsc_ahash \- ahash shared descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cnstr_shdsc_ahash
.BI "(u32 * const desc "  ","
.BI "struct alginfo *adata "  ","
.BI "u32 state "  ","
.BI "int digestsize "  ","
.BI "int ctx_len "  ","
.BI "bool import_ctx "  ","
.BI "int era "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "desc" 12
pointer to buffer used for descriptor construction
.IP "adata" 12
pointer to authentication transform definitions.
A split key is required for SEC Era < 6; the size of the split key
is specified in this case.
Valid algorithm values - one of OP_ALG_ALGSEL_{MD5, SHA1, SHA224,
SHA256, SHA384, SHA512}.
.IP "state" 12
algorithm state OP_ALG_AS_{INIT, FINALIZE, INITFINALIZE, UPDATE}
.IP "digestsize" 12
algorithm's digest size
.IP "ctx_len" 12
size of Context Register
.IP "import_ctx" 12
true if previous Context Register needs to be restored
must be true for ahash update and final
must be false for for ahash first and digest
.IP "era" 12
SEC Era
